Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal dysfunction (elevated creatinine, proteinuria), mild metabolic acidosis (low CO₂, high chloride), and hypoglycemia with low HbA1c, suggesting chronic low glucose. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, ketonuria, bilirubinuria, and abnormal appearance, indicating possible nephrotic syndrome or advanced kidney disease. No evidence of urinary infection. Immediate nephrology evaluation is recommended.
